The executive secretary of the Plateau State Christian Pilgrims Welfare Board, Rev. Fr. George Gorap, has called on the Federal Ministry of Aviation to upgrade the Yakubu Gowon Airport, Jos, to international status so that the state could airlift intending Christian pilgrims straight from the airport to Israel. Gorap made this call recently in Abuja during an interview with newsmen. He added that apart from airlifting Christian pilgrims from the airport, it would also boost the tourism and agricultural potential of Plateau State. Preparations for Argungu fishing festival hot up I’ll leverage on my experience to advance Lagos tourism… ‘Ultimate Love’ introduces show’s pivotal figure, ‘Aunty’ Will Burna Boy grab a Grammy this weekend? He thanked Governor Simon Lalong for his efforts and commitment in actualising the airport project, adding that the state has become the leading light as far as Christian pilgrimage in Nigeria is concerned. He commended Governor Lalong’s administration for sponsoring more Christian pilgrims to the Holy Land than his predecessors. He explained that the driving force behind the high number of pilgrims being sponsored by the governor was because of his genuine faith in God and his conviction that pilgrimage is a veritable tool for spiritual rebirth and transformation. Gorap further commended the Plateau pilgrims for maintaining good conduct in the past pilgrimage exercise while applauding the conduct of the 2019 general pilgrimage exercise organised by the NCPC. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURA